# Agent Instructions

## Project Shape

- Package lives under `src/__SPECX_PACKAGE_NAME__`.
- The starter core behavior lives under `src/__SPECX_PACKAGE_NAME__/core/health/`.
- Add further application behavior under `src/__SPECX_PACKAGE_NAME__/core/<scope>/`.
- Delivery belongs under `src/__SPECX_PACKAGE_NAME__/delivery/<framework>/` and remains
  separate from core behavior when a delivery technology is added.
- Scope-owned technical adapters belong under
  `src/__SPECX_PACKAGE_NAME__/core/<scope>/infrastructure/<technology>/`.
- Shared technical resources belong under `src/__SPECX_PACKAGE_NAME__/infrastructure/`.
- DI composition lives in `src/__SPECX_PACKAGE_NAME__/ioc/container.py`.
- Foundation bases come from `specx.core.foundation`, `specx.delivery.foundation`, or
  `specx.infrastructure.foundation`.
- Do not create empty architecture packages. Add a local `foundation/` only for a real
  project-local base category or stateful framework base.

## Commands

- Install: `uv sync --locked --all-groups`
- Full check: `make check`
- Lint/type/format/architecture check: `make lint`
- Format/fix: `make format`
- Tests: `make test`

## Architecture Rules

- Keep core independent from delivery, IOC, databases, network clients, and frameworks.
- Resolve application classes from `get_container()` at runtime; core classes never access
  the container directly.
- Use cases accept one same-file command or query.
- Use cases return DTOs, not entities.
- Query use cases must not call repository mutators.
- Core services choose `BasePureService`, `BaseReadService`, or `BaseEffectService` and do
  not own unit-of-work lifecycle.
- Persistence use cases inject a `UnitOfWorkManager`; they do not inject repositories,
  active UoWs, sessions, engines, or concrete infrastructure adapters directly.
- Delivery controllers call injected use cases and do not import infrastructure.
- Configure runtime logging once through `LoggingConfigurator` under top-level
  `infrastructure/logging` when the project gains a runtime entrypoint.
- Do not inject loggers or register `logging.Logger` in the DI container.
- Every project source class inherits an explicit packaged or justified local foundation
  base and includes a scoped docstring with a concrete `Example:` block.
- Keep every `__init__.py` empty.
- specx uses `select = ["ALL"]`; technology rules activate only when their project surface
  is present.
- Ruff enables every rule family with `select = ["ALL"]`; keep every ignored rule narrowly
  scoped and comment each ignored code with a plain-language rule description.

## Tests

- Mirror real source behavior under `tests/unit` or `tests/integration` with flat
  `test_<module>.py` files.
- Add test packages and fixtures only when real tests require them.
- Use `make lint` for built-in specx policy; add a programmatic pytest wrapper only
  for project-specific custom rules.
- Keep one-off test doubles in the test module that uses them and reused unit doubles in
  mirrored capability, gateway, or repository test packages.
- Do not create harnesses, target factories, grouped mock fixtures, or filler tests.
